## Recommended next three transplantation tasks

Detailed reasoning in `transplantation_readiness.md`.

### 1. Conditioning / ULP primitive (GAP-003)

**Methodology citation:** `SUBSTRATE_CONSTRUCTION.md §9 step 1` explicitly names the conditioning primitive ("instrument geometry on the IEEE 754 float lattice") as the prerequisite for V3 transplants and most subsequent substrate work.

**Capability spread:** VERY HIGH. Closes DRY-003 (10+ duplicated `ulp_*` helpers); unlocks GAP-004 (BACL grain), GAP-005 (K_G), GAP-006 (four_form), and the entire BACL/c2/Conjecture-C transplant chain.

**Why first:** the substrate construction methodology document tells us so. Its absence forces every downstream transplant to depend on ad-hoc ULP arithmetic.

### 2. Hardened dual-arm probe lift (GAP-011 / MIS-001)

**Why second (and parallelisable with #1):** independent of GAP-001/002/003. The probe is production-operative per `LIVE_CAMPAIGNS_LEDGER` `hardened-dual-arm-probe` V1; the only debt is lifecycle. Self-contained transplant — no new substrate primitives needed.

**Capability spread:** HIGH but localised. Closes an architectural debt; provides a worked example of the §3 methodology applied at the L3 instrument level.

**Note:** LAYER_MANIFEST.md may need a new `probes/` sub-layer to host this. The lift forces the methodology question.

### 3. Typed sqrt + typed log primitive bundle (GAP-001 + GAP-002)

**Why third:** tightly coupled (both required for `typed_log_log_slope` and `directional_alpha_probe` to clear Axiom 11′); naturally lands together; depends on GAP-003 for shared conditioning primitive composition.

**Capability spread:** VERY HIGH. Touches every Axiom-11-strict-form-violating substrate site (4 L1 primitives + 1 L2 module) and sets up the Axiom 11 → Axiom 11′ refinement transition per `SUBSTRATE_CONSTRUCTION.md §7.1`.

**Note:** the substrate-native impl can call `math.sqrt` / `math.log` internally during construction (the IEEE-754-correct rounding is already characterised by BACL + Conjecture C); the gating work is wrapping these in typed envelopes with declared status families.

